On August 6th, 2009, two speeches were scheduled to take place in Washington, DC. Christina Romer, Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers, was set to deliver remarks at the Economic Club of Washington, DC at 8:00 AM EDT. She planned to assess the impact of the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act on the economy and discuss future expectations. John Brennan, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, was scheduled to speak at the Center for Strategic and International Studies at 11:00 AM EDT. He intended to provide an overview of the President's comprehensive approach to protecting the American people from terrorism, focusing on defeating the near-term threat from al Qaeda and other transnational terrorist groups, as well as addressing the political, economic, and social factors that fuel violent extremism. The respective organizations were responsible for handling media logistics and credentialing for each event.